content.description:
Quagmire tic tacs up a slight overhang on small edges and pockets.

Sit start with a left hand sidepull and a good right hand edge. From there, pull up left to and then straight up on an assortment of small edges and pockets.
content.protection: A pair of pads. The immediate landing is great, but there is a small tree behind the landing.
content.location: It climbs the south face of Quagmire.

content.description:
Sit start at the featured arete. From there, climb straight up the featured face, and mantle atop.

There is plenty of friable rock on this one. Be careful of what you pull. This will get better with more traffic.
content.protection: A pad will work fine. The landing is very good.
content.location: It climbs the center (south) portion of Quagmire's west face.

content.description:
Stand start with hands match on the edge five feet off the deck. From there, climb straight up on an assortment of holds, and mantle atop the boulder.

There is plenty of friable rock on this one. Be careful of what you pull. This will get better with more traffic.
content.protection: A pad will work well. The landing is very good.
content.location: It climbs the north section of Quagmire's west face.

content.description: Squat start with a good right hand edge on the arete, a low left hand edge on the face, and a left heel hook matched next to it. From there, crank up to a left hand edge, move the right hand up the arete, then reach the edges below the lip, and at the lip mantle on top.
content.protection: At least a pair of pads, three would be ideal. The landing is very rough, there are several rocks, the landing is uneven, and it doesn't pad well.
content.location: It climbs the south face/southeast arete of Quagmire.
